  [1mRead README.md[22m

  [1m[3m[4mterminalcp[24m[23m[22m

  [38;2;177;185;249mhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e19a83da-e446-4ccd-9028-9c1cc0[39m
  e09a5e

  Let AI agents control interactive command-line tools like a human would.

  [1mProject Overview â€“ terminalcp[22m

  terminalcp is a Node-JS library and CLI that lets AI agents (or any
  program) control interactive command-line tools just like a human would.
  It provides a "Playwright-for-the-terminal"-style interface that can:

  â€¢ Spawn and manage any CLI process (debuggers, REPLs, build tools, etc.)
  in a pseudo-TTY.
  â€¢ Send keystrokes, special keys, and control sequences to those
  processes.
  â€¢ Read output either as a full rendered screen (for TUIs, debuggers,
  etc.) or as a raw stream (for logs, builds, etc.).
  â€¢ Run multiple sessions simultaneously, with each session persisting
  across client disconnects.
  â€¢ Allow users to attach to AI-spawned sessions (like screen/tmux) to
  watch or intervene.

  [1m### Key Features[22m

  â€¢ Debugging: drive LLDB, GDB, pdb, etc., step-by-step.
  â€¢ AI Collaboration: run other AI tools (Claude, Gemini, etc.) as
  subprocesses.
  â€¢ REPL & Shell Interaction: Python, Node, Ruby, database shells, etc.
  â€¢ Process Management: start, stop, list, and kill sessions via JSON
  commands (MCP) or a CLI.
  â€¢ Two output modes
    â€¢ Terminal mode (stdout) â€“ full screen with colors, ideal for TUIs.
    â€¢ Stream mode (stream) â€“ raw output, optionally incremental and
  ANSI-stripped.
  â€¢ MCP Server: exposes a single terminalcp tool that accepts JSON actions
  (start, stdin, stdout, stream, stop, etc.).
  â€¢ CLI: terminalcp start|stop|attach|stdout|stream|... for manual use.
  â€¢ Programmatic API: TerminalManager class for programmatic control
  (start, sendInput, stdout, stream, stop).

  [1m### Architecture[22m

  1. TerminalManager â€“ core PTY manager (node-pty + xterm.js headless)
  handling I/O and terminal emulation.
  2. TerminalServer â€“ background process listening on a Unix socket,
  managing all sessions.
  3. TerminalClient â€“ communication layer used by both MCP server and CLI.
  4. User Interfaces â€“ MCP server (for AI agents) and CLI (for humans) both
   talk to the server.

  [1m### Typical Use Cases[22m

  â€¢ AI-driven debugging (LLDB, GDB).
  â€¢ Running and monitoring builds.
  â€¢ Automating REPLs or interactive tools.
  â€¢ Testing TUI applications.
  â€¢ Attaching to AI-spawned processes from a terminal (like tmux/screen).

  [1m### Getting Started[22m

  1. Install the MCP server (npx @mariozechner/terminalcp@latest --mcp) and
   add it to your MCP client (VS Code, Claude, Cursor, etc.).
  2. Use JSON commands via the MCP tool or the CLI to start processes, send
   input, and retrieve output.
  3. Use the TerminalManager API for programmatic control in Node.js apps.

  In short: terminalcp provides a robust, programmatic way for AI agents
  (and developers) to spawn, control, and monitor interactive terminal
  programs, with full PTY emulation, multi-session support, and both
  programmatic and CLI interfaces.
